on the face of it,

1007
01:12:50,160 --> 01:12:53,440
she's not on the other side of the world.

1008
01:12:53,960 --> 01:12:54,840
That was unexpected.

1009
01:12:56,920 --> 01:12:58,520
You have her first and last names?

1010
01:12:59,040 --> 01:12:59,960
[woman] Of course.

1011
01:13:00,520 --> 01:13:02,160
Which I can't have, obviously.

1012
01:13:02,680 --> 01:13:04,560
-Nope.
-That's right.

1013
01:13:04,640 --> 01:13:06,880
What's the origin of her names?

1014
01:13:06,960 --> 01:13:08,920
Can you tell?

1015
01:13:09,000 --> 01:13:11,200
I can't answer questions about that.

1016
01:13:11,280 --> 01:13:14,400
-I'm wondering if they sound foreign.
-[woman] I can imagine.

1017
01:13:14,480 --> 01:13:17,800
Is it a… I mean,
could it be a French name?

1018
01:13:19,800 --> 01:13:20,640
[woman] Yes.

1019
01:13:21,120 --> 01:13:22,000
-Okay.
-[woman] It's--

1020
01:13:22,080 --> 01:13:26,560
I mean, it's not at all…
It's not extraordinary or anything.

1021
01:13:27,720 --> 01:13:29,720
-Or especially unusual.
-Okay.

1022
01:13:31,320 --> 01:13:33,880
You know so much more than me.
It's horrible.

1023
01:13:35,040 --> 01:13:38,520
Do people address their parents
formally or informally when they meet?

1024
01:13:38,600 --> 01:13:39,560
There's no rule.

1025
01:13:40,320 --> 01:13:43,400
There's no rule.
Each person decides for themselves.

1026
01:13:43,480 --> 01:13:45,200
Everyone is free to choose

1027
01:13:45,280 --> 01:13:48,760
depending on what they experience or feel.

1028
01:13:49,680 --> 01:13:51,240
Even what you call them.

1029
01:13:53,240 --> 01:13:55,560
When people…

1030
01:13:55,640 --> 01:13:57,640
We might suggest, for example,

1031
01:13:57,720 --> 01:13:59,960
that people write a letter

1032
01:14:00,040 --> 01:14:02,240
to the biological parent,
if they agree to it.

1033
01:14:02,320 --> 01:14:04,280
-That they exchange letters.
-Of course.

1034
01:14:05,040 --> 01:14:05,880
For letters,

1035
01:14:06,640 --> 01:14:09,760
you write to the person
according to how you see them,

1036
01:14:09,840 --> 01:14:10,760
how you feel.

1037
01:14:10,840 --> 01:14:14,320
You can write "Mrs." and her last name,
you can write "Mom"…

1038
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:16,760
It's not straightforward. And…

1039
01:14:16,840 --> 01:14:18,680
At the same time, it speaks volumes.

1040
01:14:18,760 --> 01:14:21,560
You have to say things as you feel them.

1041
01:14:21,640 --> 01:14:25,000
Which part of France does she live in?
Can't I know that either?

1042
01:14:25,080 --> 01:14:27,600
-[woman] She lives in the Southwest.
-Okay.

1043
01:14:31,160 --> 01:14:32,120
That's big.

1044
01:14:34,920 --> 01:14:37,160
You know,
you could tell me the town. I mean…

1045
01:14:37,240 --> 01:14:40,120
I'm sure a lot of people live there.
Yeah, okay.

1046
01:14:40,840 --> 01:14:41,880
Uh…

1047
01:14:42,680 --> 01:14:45,720
Would you like to write…

1048
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:48,920
-Yes.
-[woman] …to her?

1049
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:50,760
I suggest you do that.

1050
01:14:50,840 --> 01:14:53,240
But I can't guarantee I'll be able to…

1051
01:14:53,320 --> 01:14:55,960
I'll explain the circumstances in which

1052
01:14:56,040 --> 01:14:57,400
I can give her the message.

1053
01:14:58,040 --> 01:15:02,560
If I manage to reach her on the telephone,

1054
01:15:02,640 --> 01:15:05,400
I'll tell her about you,
what you're hoping for,

1055
01:15:05,480 --> 01:15:07,920
our conversations, all that.

1056
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:10,480
-But those are just my words.
-Of course.

1057
01:15:10,560 --> 01:15:12,920
What I can do is tell her,

1058
01:15:13,000 --> 01:15:15,160
"Olivier has written you a letter."

1059
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:17,560
"Would you permit me to read it to you

1060
01:15:17,640 --> 01:15:19,520
and then forward it to you?"

1061
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:21,880
-Reading it to her first.
-That would be amazing.

1062
01:15:22,400 --> 01:15:25,400
-[woman] I've had people say no before.
-Okay.

1063
01:15:26,520 --> 01:15:29,680
[woman] People who say,
"No, I don't want that,"

1064
01:15:29,760 --> 01:15:31,560
because then it makes you too real.

1065
01:15:32,120 --> 01:15:33,000
Mm. Yes.

1066
01:15:35,440 --> 01:15:37,800
[woman] For the moment, you're a baby

1067
01:15:37,880 --> 01:15:40,480
who was entrusted into state care…

1068
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:41,960
Uh…

1069
01:15:43,080 --> 01:15:46,760
I think, in the file,
it said she didn't see you.

1070
01:15:46,840 --> 01:15:48,720
-No, I don't think she did.
-[woman] Right.

1071
01:15:49,280 --> 01:15:52,400
Mrs. Lamothe told me
it was a bit of a mystery.

1072
01:15:52,480 --> 01:15:55,520
She took it to mean
that she didn't see me.

1073
01:15:55,600 --> 01:15:58,000
-She had a Cesarean.
-[woman] I read it. I'm positive.

1074
01:15:58,080 --> 01:16:00,520
Yeah, I know, but she had a Cesarean,

1075
01:16:00,600 --> 01:16:02,200
so they put her to sleep

1076
01:16:03,160 --> 01:16:04,120
and took the baby.

1077
01:16:51,120 --> 01:16:51,960
[Olivier] Dear…

1078
01:16:53,520 --> 01:16:54,440
Three little dots.

1079
01:16:56,600 --> 01:16:59,040
I obviously don't know
how to start this letter.

1080
01:17:00,000 --> 01:17:02,240
Which last name. Which first name.

1081
01:17:03,240 --> 01:17:05,160
Should I address you formally or not?

1082
01:17:06,520 --> 01:17:08,600
I could say
I've spent a year looking for you.

1083
01:17:09,120 --> 01:17:11,800
But my approach
in this letter is to be honest.

1084
01:17:12,920 --> 01:17:14,480
So I've spent 32 years looking.

1085
01:17:15,000 --> 01:17:17,800
Thirty-two years of doubt,
but 32 years of happiness too.

1086
01:17:17,880 --> 01:17:19,200
Thirty-two years of questions.

1087
01:17:20,800 --> 01:17:22,080
Thirty-two years of love,

1088
01:17:22,160 --> 01:17:24,400
of solitude, of worry.

1089
01:17:26,400 --> 01:17:28,840
My position is both simple
and very complicated.

1090
01:17:29,440 --> 01:17:30,920
You are my biological mother.

1091
01:17:32,240 --> 01:17:33,680
And for that, I thank you.

1092
01:17:35,560 --> 01:17:37,720
I thank you for the person I am today.

1093
01:17:39,920 --> 01:17:41,680
I thank you for giving birth to me.

1094
01:17:43,120 --> 01:17:45,760
But also because I've had
so much love in my life.

1095
01:17:46,720 --> 01:17:49,080
So many values, so much protection,

1096
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:51,120
to face a world that can be very tough

1097
01:17:52,600 --> 01:17:53,920
and does you no favors.

1098
01:17:55,320 --> 01:17:56,960
I've had a great family.

1099
01:17:57,040 --> 01:17:58,440
I have a great family.

1100
01:17:59,320 --> 01:18:00,400
One that loves me.

1101
01:18:01,400 --> 01:18:02,240
I have friends.

1102
01:18:07,360 --> 01:18:08,960
My parents who dried my eyes,

1103
01:18:09,640 --> 01:18:12,080
comforted me, and wiped away my tears.

1104
01:18:12,160 --> 01:18:14,440
Who heard my first laughs,
saw my first steps

1105
01:18:15,440 --> 01:18:16,400
and felt my pain.

1106
01:18:17,600 --> 01:18:19,200
But I thank you for all of that.

1107
01:18:20,240 --> 01:18:23,920
But within all this,
I've become an adult full of doubts.

1108
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:26,440
Inexplicable fears.

1109
01:18:27,640 --> 01:18:29,400
And maybe only you can help me.

1110
01:18:37,160 --> 01:18:38,560
-[Olivier] Mohammed.
-Yes?

1111
01:18:38,640 --> 01:18:40,800
[Olivier] Want to hear
something funny that happened?

1112
01:18:43,920 --> 01:18:47,080
-[Mohammed] What is it?
-I read an article, and…

1113
01:18:48,760 --> 01:18:51,240
It was about me,
and the title was The Wonder Boy.

1114
01:18:51,880 --> 01:18:54,040
-[Mohammed] "The Wonder Boy"?
-Yeah.

1115
01:18:54,120 --> 01:18:56,200
-Do know what that is?
-[Mohammed] No.

1116
01:18:57,560 --> 01:18:59,880
[Olivier] A wonder boy is a boy

1117
01:18:59,960 --> 01:19:01,240
who has achieved success

1118
01:19:02,440 --> 01:19:05,120
without necessarily much luck in his past,

1119
01:19:05,200 --> 01:19:06,960
who fought to make it.

1120
01:19:07,040 --> 01:19:08,040
He's a success

1121
01:19:09,520 --> 01:19:10,960
who you could say is…

1122
01:19:11,040 --> 01:19:12,080
[Mohammed] Deserving?

1123
01:19:12,600 --> 01:19:14,400
Not deserving. He's a success…

1124
01:19:22,640 --> 01:19:24,240
that wasn't supposed to happen.

1125
01:19:29,880 --> 01:19:31,400
Do you think I'm a wonder boy?

1126
01:19:31,920 --> 01:19:36,080
["Unforgettable"
by French Montana feat. Swae Lee]

1127
01:19:46,040 --> 01:19:48,320
Olivier has not met
his biological mother yet.

1128
01:19:48,400 --> 01:19:50,040
"I'm afraid of a second rejection,

1129
01:19:50,120 --> 01:19:52,920
opening the wound left by this woman
who gave birth to me.

1130
01:19:53,000 --> 01:19:55,960
My only hope is that
she recognizes herself in this film."

1131
01:19:56,040 --> 01:20:00,480
["Unforgettable"
by French Montana feat. Swae Lee]

1132
